9.7 Summary of Implementation

The proposed architecture is built from space‑qualified components and integrates the theoretical developments into a practical system. Key features:

· Distributed: No single point of failure; each tile operates autonomously with local information.
· Fault‑tolerant: Redundant communication, power backup, and health management.
· Real‑time: 10 Hz control loop with limited ADMM iterations, suitable for embedded hardware.
· Safe: Formal safety certificates from HJI reachability; event‑triggering and switched ISS analysis guarantee stability under communication loss.

This implementation lays the groundwork for future experimental validation and eventual flight demonstration.

Chapter 10: Validation Roadmap

This chapter outlines the theoretical validation of the proposed hierarchical distributed MPC architecture. While experimental and simulation-based validation are essential for eventual deployment, the focus here is on mathematical verification, consistency checks, and analytical comparisons that establish the soundness of the framework. Future experimental work (co‑simulation, plasma wind‑tunnel tests, hardware‑in‑the‑loop) is beyond the scope of this thesis but is outlined as a natural continuation.

